Tan Crone (born 's-Hertogenbosch, Netherlands, March 2, 1930; died Wassenaar, Netherlands, January 17, 2009) was a noted Dutch classical pianist.
Her recording with John Bröcheler in 1979 won the "Preis der deutschen Schallplattenkritik".
She died at Wassenaar, Netherlands, January 17, 2009.

1984 - Charles Ives: Songs (2 CDs) (Etcetera)
